<bdy>

<b>List of numerical computational geometry topics</b> enumerates the topics of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../927/176927.xml">
computational geometry</link> that deals with geometric objects as continuous entities and applies methods and algorithms of nature characteristic to <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../506/21506.xml">
numerical analysis</link>. This area is also called "machine geometry", computer-aided geometric design, and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../632/511632.xml">
geometric modelling</link>.<p>

See <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../840/2920840.xml">
List of combinatorial computational geometry topics</link> for another flavor of computational geometry that states problems in terms of geometric objects as <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../492/8492.xml">
discrete</link> entities and hence the methods of their solution are mostly theories and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../775/775.xml">
algorithm</link>s of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../170/5170.xml">
combinatorial</link> character.</p>

